‹g¬]<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1209";s:4:"name";s:13:"Endometriosis";s:4:"slug";s:13:"endometriosis";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1209";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:3911:"<span style="font-weight: 400;">Endometriosis is a very painful disorder which occurs when the tissues usually found inside the uterus begins to develop outside the uterus. It only occurs in women at their fertility age. In fact, 10% of women in the world have endometriosis. It is the second most common gynecological problem in the world. Endometriosis causes severe pain - most especially during the menstrual cycle. It may develop into fertility issues.</span>

<b>Symptoms Of Endometriosis</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The main symptom of this disorder is pelvic pain, usually linked with menstrual periods. Other signs and symptoms include:</span>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pain During Intercourse</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Excessive bleeding</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">In some cases, infertility</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fatigue</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Diarrhea</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">However, the intensity of the pain does not determine the severity of the condition.</span>

<b>Causes Of Endometriosis</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Although doctors don't know the actual cause of endometriosis, previous explanations linked its cause to menstrual and immune system disorder.</span>

<b>Risk Factors For Endometriosis</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Many factors trigger the risk of developing endometriosis, they include:</span>

<b>Family history: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">If a member of your family has endometriosis, your chances of getting it are high. Endometriosis can be gotten both paternally and maternally.</span>

<b>Conditions that alter the regular menstrual flow: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the most common medical conditions associated with endometriosis is retrograde menstrual flow or a backward menstrual flow.</span>

<b>Abnormality of the immune system: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Abnormal functioning of the immune system contributes to endometriosis.</span>

<b>Other risk factors include:</b>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you‚Äôve never given birth before</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Starting periods earlier</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Experiencing menopause at an older age</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">A very short menstrual cycle</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Long term menstrual period - for example, 7 days or longer.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Low BMI</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">¬†</span><b>Treatment Of Endometriosis</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Treating endometriosis often involves surgery or medication. Your doctor's approach depends on the severity of your condition. At first, doctors usually start with the conservative treatment approach and may lead to surgery (if the former fails).</span>

